genresAdvancedInfo.name: virgin islands reggae
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Virgin Islands reggae is a style of reggae music that originated in the Virgin Islands, a group of islands in the Caribbean. It is characterized by its laid-back, groovy rhythms and its focus on social and political issues. Virgin Islands reggae often incorporates elements of other Caribbean music styles, such as calypso and soca, and it has been influenced by the music of Bob Marley and other Jamaican reggae artists.
